<div class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="title has-text-centered">About the Project</h1>

    <div class="content">
      <p>
        The <strong>Music Genius</strong> is designed to provide music enthusiasts with an intuitive,
        engaging platform to explore and discover music across various genres.
        The project integrates with the <strong>Last.fm API</strong> to fetch and display tracks.
        Built using <strong>Ruby on Rails</strong> for the backend, with a <strong>SQLite database</strong>
        to manage artists, genres, and tracks, and styled with <strong>Bulma CSS</strong>, this application
        merges robust functionality with a clean, user-friendly design.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="image is-200x200">
      <%= image_tag "project_erd.png" %>
    </figure>

    <h2 class="subtitle has-text-centered mt-6">Key Features</h2>
    <div class="columns is-multiline">
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="box">
          <h3 class="subtitle">Discover Music by Genre</h3>
          <p>Users can explore popular tracks across a wide range of genres.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="box">
          <h3 class="subtitle">Artist and Track Details</h3>
          <p>Each track includes detailed information about its artist and associated genres. Users can explore individual artist pages and check their songs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="box">
          <h3 class="subtitle">Responsive and Modern UI</h3>
          <p>The application is built with Bulma, providing a visually appealing, responsive layout.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="box">
          <h2 class="subtitle has-text-centered">Technology Stack</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Ruby on Rails</li>
            <li><strong>Database:</strong> SQLite</li>
            <li><strong>API Integration:</strong> Last.fm API</li>
            <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Bulma CSS</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
